        {
          "name": "player",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The player for whom the strategist should plan a move. This object must be in the current game model’s "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkgamemodel/1490287-players"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " array."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An object describing the move found by the strategist."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method looks ahead at the possible moves for the specified player, as well as possible future moves by other players on subsequent turns (according to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkminmaxstrategist/1501226-maxlookaheaddepth"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property) and examines the state of the game model resulting from each possible move. Your game model class provides a score for each state in its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkgamemodel/1490281-scoreforplayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method, allowing the strategist to find the sequence of future moves that maximizes the score for the specified player and return the first move in that sequence."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The object returned is an instance of your custom class implementing the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkgamemodelupdate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " protocol. This object was created in your game model’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkgamemodel/1490288-gamemodelupdatesforplayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method, describing in your game’s terms a possible move. Examine that information to make use of the strategist’s selection. For example, you could implement a computer-controlled player by performing the selected move, or provide hints to a human player by indicating the selected move in your game’s user interface."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If multiple possible moves are tied for the best score and the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkstrategist/1501317-randomsource"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property is not "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "nil"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", this method randomly selects from among the tied moves."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method returns "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "nil"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " if the specified player is invalid or has no available moves."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
